'''Old Kaduna Airport''' is an airport serving [[Kaduna]], a city in the [[Kaduna State]] of [[Nigeria]].<ref>[http://worldaerodata.com/wad.cgi?id=NI45711 Old Kaduna Airport] at World Aero Data. Source: [[DAFIF]].</ref> It was replaced by [[Kaduna Airport]], located 10 miles to the northwest.
It appears to be the headquarters of [[NAF Training Command]] with a flying training group and a ground training group at the base. The command is chiefly responsible for implementing NAF training policies. Ground training is also provided for support services and technical personnel.<ref>See http://www.nigerianairforce.net/nafstructure/TC.aspx</ref> :301 Flying Training School, Kaduna :303 Flying Training School, Kano :320 Technical Training Group, Kaduna :325 Ground Training Group, Kaduna
